parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Tire Failure (Tread Separation, Blowouts, and Uneven Wear)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.

blowouts
uneven wear
vibration
thumping noise

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the spare tire holder can cause the spare tire to drop out from under the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Spare tire drops out from under the vehicle
cable breaks or corrodes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rim cracks can cause air leaks, leading to tire failure, loss of control, and accidents.

air leaks
slow leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences extended stopping distances
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor

the brakes fail to stop the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor failure can cause uneven braking, extended stopping distances, and loss of control, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The brake rotors warp or wear out prematurely
the vehicle experiences vibration or pulsation when applying brakes
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unintentionally, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and accidents.
